  "text": "Django's CSRF protection is implemented across multiple files forming a comprehensive validation chain. The primary entry point is the CsrfViewMiddleware class in django/middleware/csrf.py, which implements the core CSRF protection mechanism. The middleware's process_view method (line 414) orchestrates the CSRF validation by checking for CSRF tokens and validating them against stored secrets.\n\nThe token validation logic is centered in the _check_token method (line 349), which retrieves the CSRF secret via _get_secret (line 221) and validates the incoming request token. The token format is verified using _check_token_format (line 130), which ensures tokens have correct length and valid characters.\n\nThe critical timing-attack-resistant comparison happens in _does_token_match (line 143), which first unmasks tokens using _unmask_cipher_token (line 71) if necessary, then uses constant_time_compare from django/utils/crypto.py (line 65) to safely compare tokens. The constant_time_compare function (line 65 in crypto.py) delegates to Python's secrets.compare_digest, providing protection against timing attacks.\n\nToken generation and masking is handled by _mask_cipher_secret (line 59) and get_token (line 96), with token rotation supported through rotate_token (line 117).\n\nThe decorator-based CSRF protection is provided through django/views/decorators/csrf.py, with csrf_protect being the main decorator that applies the same CsrfViewMiddleware validation on a per-view basis. Alternative decorators include csrf_exempt (line 50) to exclude views, requires_csrf_token (line 22) for views that need the token without enforcement, and ensure_csrf_cookie (line 42) to force CSRF cookie generation.\n\nTemplate support is provided through django/template/defaulttags.py with the CsrfTokenNode class (line 73) and csrf_token function (line 705) that renders the hidden input field containing the CSRF token. The token is made available to templates via the context processor in django/template/context_processors.py (line 18) using the get_token function.\n\nCSRF failure handling is implemented in django/views/csrf.py with the csrf_failure view (line 22). Security validation of CSRF configuration is performed by checks in django/core/checks/security/csrf.py, including checks for middleware presence, CSRF_COOKIE_SECURE setting, and proper CSRF failure view configuration.\n\nThe complete validation chain for a POST request is: CsrfViewMiddleware.process_view → origin/referer checking → _check_token → _get_secret → _check_token_format → _does_token_match → _unmask_cipher_token → constant_time_compare (using secrets.compare_digest for timing-attack resistance)."
}

